1
00:02:06,345 --> 00:02:08,144
Ask your mom

2
00:02:08,225 --> 00:02:10,705
why your dad used to call you

3
00:02:10,785 --> 00:02:11,945
a bastard.

4
00:02:12,025 --> 00:02:14,025
Do you and Uncle Saen
still love each other?

5
00:02:14,105 --> 00:02:17,105
Am I really a bastard like Dad said?

6
00:02:17,184 --> 00:02:18,665
Don't say that.

7
00:02:18,745 --> 00:02:21,624
Is anyone inside the house?
Come out this instant.

8
00:02:22,785 --> 00:02:24,825
Did you see the way
they were looking at us?

9
00:02:24,904 --> 00:02:28,385
Do you really think
they came here to get Tofu's memory back?

10
00:02:30,305 --> 00:02:31,985
You should live in the present.

11
00:02:32,064 --> 00:02:35,464
You should use the time to worry
about your loved ones' feelings.

12
00:02:36,184 --> 00:02:37,665
You are confusing Tofu

13
00:02:38,464 --> 00:02:41,505
by expressing countless concerns
toward your ex-boyfriend.

14
00:02:41,585 --> 00:02:44,145
She said…

15
00:02:44,225 --> 00:02:47,344
I'm showing symptoms of Alzheimer's.

16
00:02:47,425 --> 00:02:49,385
Since your mom is already sick,

17
00:02:52,425 --> 00:02:55,105
why don't we find a way to help her?

18
00:03:00,385 --> 00:03:04,265
I suspect there is still some evidence
remaining in the house.

19
00:03:09,624 --> 00:03:12,425
Our forensics team even found the blood

20
00:03:12,504 --> 00:03:14,105
that was wiped clean.

21
00:03:15,184 --> 00:03:17,904
Do you think
they could've missed something?

22
00:03:33,545 --> 00:03:34,985
A bit of broken tile.

23
00:03:36,105 --> 00:03:37,425
How did it get there?

24
00:03:37,504 --> 00:03:39,145
And how did you know?

25
00:03:41,825 --> 00:03:44,985
I found a bit of broken tile
in a cactus at Tatarn's house.

26
00:03:46,624 --> 00:03:48,344
Could it be related to the case?

27
00:03:49,665 --> 00:03:51,425
Do you mind checking it for me?

28
00:04:57,264 --> 00:04:58,185
Lieutenant Kong.

29
00:04:58,264 --> 00:05:01,785
Can you find an old picture of the house,
so we can compare?

30
00:05:01,865 --> 00:05:03,425
Yes, sir.

31
00:05:21,985 --> 00:05:23,225
Hey.

32
00:05:23,785 --> 00:05:24,985
Why did you come here?

33
00:05:25,065 --> 00:05:26,704
I told you not to come here.

34
00:05:26,785 --> 00:05:29,464
My employee said
the police went to Tatarn's house.

35
00:05:31,584 --> 00:05:34,665
See? Those kids
are really causing us trouble.

36
00:05:35,584 --> 00:05:38,225
You should've discussed with me
before letting them in.

37
00:05:39,905 --> 00:05:41,385
You're too careless.

38
00:05:42,264 --> 00:05:43,905
You're the careless one.

39
00:05:43,985 --> 00:05:46,905
If you hadn't stepped in,
it would've been much easier.

40
00:05:46,985 --> 00:05:49,185
I stepped in
because I was worried about you.

41
00:05:50,464 --> 00:05:54,345
If you hadn't attacked him,
I wouldn't have to put myself in danger.

42
00:05:55,345 --> 00:05:56,665
Are you threatening me?

43
00:05:56,745 --> 00:05:58,024
I'm just trying to warn you.

44
00:05:59,065 --> 00:06:00,985
Stop trying.

45
00:06:01,065 --> 00:06:02,625
I won't back down.

46
00:06:03,385 --> 00:06:05,505
What do you hope to gain?

47
00:06:05,584 --> 00:06:08,185
You know full well
that you don't have enough influence.

48
00:06:08,264 --> 00:06:10,545
It's not going to bring about any change.

49
00:06:10,625 --> 00:06:12,545
Things might not change today,

50
00:06:12,625 --> 00:06:14,345
but they will in the future.

51
00:06:14,945 --> 00:06:16,665
Time is on our side.

52
00:06:16,745 --> 00:06:19,345
We have time to win, to fight, to lose.

53
00:06:19,425 --> 00:06:22,824
Winning might take time,

54
00:06:22,904 --> 00:06:24,545
but that day will come.

55
00:06:24,625 --> 00:06:26,345
But power is on their side.

56
00:06:26,425 --> 00:06:28,985
We have to get that power on our side.

57
00:06:29,065 --> 00:06:33,144
The people should have the power,
so that problems can be solved.

58
00:06:34,385 --> 00:06:37,745
Am I supposed to give up
and be a coward like you?

59
00:06:37,824 --> 00:06:40,945
Should I give in to power,
abandon my principles,

60
00:06:41,024 --> 00:06:43,185
and behave immorally like you?

61
00:06:43,865 --> 00:06:45,024
I can't do it.

62
00:06:58,105 --> 00:06:59,425
Mr. Saen…

63
00:06:59,985 --> 00:07:01,665
hit your nephew's head.

64
00:07:01,745 --> 00:07:03,665
Secretly keep an eye on him

65
00:07:03,745 --> 00:07:04,904
and keep me posted.

66
00:07:04,985 --> 00:07:06,305
I'm heading there now.

67
00:07:27,105 --> 00:07:29,185
I stayed put like you told me to,

68
00:07:29,264 --> 00:07:30,985
but trouble still found us.

69
00:07:31,625 --> 00:07:32,865
Are you sure

70
00:07:32,945 --> 00:07:36,305
that nobody was in the house
other than you and your men?

71
00:07:37,105 --> 00:07:39,144
Why? Who do you suspect?

72
00:07:39,225 --> 00:07:40,785
Tofu.

73
00:07:41,584 --> 00:07:43,545
He might actually know Tarn.

74
00:07:44,305 --> 00:07:47,545
He could have been in the house that day
and has seen the whole thing.

75
00:07:48,144 --> 00:07:50,264
That's why he moved
to the house next door,

76
00:07:50,344 --> 00:07:53,704
and lied about his amnesia
in order to keep an eye on us.

77
00:07:55,105 --> 00:07:57,144
Did you see the way he looked at us?

78
00:07:57,225 --> 00:07:58,704
It's as if he knows something.

79
00:07:59,385 --> 00:08:01,584
Think about it.
He went to the house yesterday.

80
00:08:01,665 --> 00:08:03,704
Today, the police went
there for something.

81
00:08:11,264 --> 00:08:12,625
How did this happen?

82
00:08:14,344 --> 00:08:17,305
We don't know for sure what the cause is.

83
00:08:17,385 --> 00:08:19,185
According to studies,

84
00:08:19,264 --> 00:08:23,425
there are multiple factors that can be
the cause of Alzheimer's disease.

85
00:08:23,505 --> 00:08:25,904
It may be due to age,

86
00:08:25,985 --> 00:08:27,584
genetics,

87
00:08:27,665 --> 00:08:29,704
brain trauma,

88
00:08:29,784 --> 00:08:32,385
or brain infections.

89
00:08:33,345 --> 00:08:36,424
These can cause changes in brain cells.

90
00:08:36,945 --> 00:08:40,264
As brain cells deteriorate,

91
00:08:41,544 --> 00:08:44,585
the patients start losing memories.

92
00:08:45,745 --> 00:08:47,945
This affects thinking

93
00:08:48,025 --> 00:08:49,225
and decision-making.

94
00:08:49,825 --> 00:08:51,945
They will be forgetful,

95
00:08:52,025 --> 00:08:54,145
and won't be able to learn new things.

96
00:09:00,064 --> 00:09:01,544
To be honest,

97
00:09:01,625 --> 00:09:03,825
the chance of Alzheimer's disease

98
00:09:03,905 --> 00:09:05,945
for someone
in their fifties like you is slim.

99
00:09:06,025 --> 00:09:09,985
Especially for someone
who has had a mental illness,

100
00:09:10,064 --> 00:09:11,945
the chance is incredibly slim.

101
00:09:14,705 --> 00:09:18,304
But looking at your symptoms,

102
00:09:18,385 --> 00:09:21,064
it's most likely

103
00:09:21,665 --> 00:09:23,745
that it is Alzheimer's disease.

104
00:09:25,585 --> 00:09:27,865
But we should still monitor the symptoms.

105
00:09:30,665 --> 00:09:32,625
Why didn't you tell me about it last time?

106
00:09:38,705 --> 00:09:40,145
I was afraid you would worry.

107
00:09:42,505 --> 00:09:44,825
I thought I would tell you about it
after your trip.

108
00:09:45,544 --> 00:09:48,304
I didn't expect that incident
in Chiang Mai.

109
00:09:55,184 --> 00:09:56,585
It doesn't matter.

110
00:09:57,345 --> 00:09:59,345
Now that we know about it,

111
00:10:00,585 --> 00:10:03,424
let's do our best
to look after her from now on.

112
00:10:04,345 --> 00:10:05,345
Exactly.

113
00:10:05,905 --> 00:10:09,105
We can't cure Alzheimer's disease,

114
00:10:09,184 --> 00:10:13,304
but if we find out and treat it early,
and take good care of ourselves,

115
00:10:13,385 --> 00:10:16,385
it will slow down the disease progression.

116
00:10:16,465 --> 00:10:20,745
We can also prevent the danger
of other complications.

117
00:10:22,625 --> 00:10:24,944
To treat Alzheimer's disease,

118
00:10:25,025 --> 00:10:27,505
you can use drugs and other methods.

119
00:10:28,785 --> 00:10:30,585
These are the drugs I'm prescribing.

120
00:10:30,665 --> 00:10:35,225
One is for temporarily reducing symptoms,

121
00:10:36,544 --> 00:10:41,985
and the other is for suppressing
brain deteriorating chemicals.

122
00:10:43,345 --> 00:10:47,225
The patient can lead
a relatively normal life.

123
00:10:48,265 --> 00:10:50,064
You will feel bright,

124
00:10:50,585 --> 00:10:54,865
which will be easier on the caretaker.

125
00:10:55,705 --> 00:10:56,905
Where's Tofu?

126
00:10:59,824 --> 00:11:01,064
Let's go, Mrs. Na.

127
00:11:01,625 --> 00:11:02,505
Shoot.

128
00:11:09,064 --> 00:11:11,585
But what's more important than drugs

129
00:11:12,665 --> 00:11:14,265
is taking care of the brain,

130
00:11:15,184 --> 00:11:17,745
along with caring
for your physical and mental health.

131
00:11:19,944 --> 00:11:22,064
Research has found

132
00:11:22,145 --> 00:11:24,905
that regular exercise

133
00:11:24,985 --> 00:11:26,985
freshens up the brain

134
00:11:28,385 --> 00:11:31,465
and extends the disease progression.

135
00:11:39,905 --> 00:11:42,304
It is also important

136
00:11:42,385 --> 00:11:46,745
for the patient to socialize
and meet up with people

137
00:11:46,824 --> 00:11:48,944
apart from household members.

138
00:12:14,385 --> 00:12:16,304
I noticed that your lights were still on.

139
00:12:17,064 --> 00:12:19,705
I realized I hadn't unpacked.

140
00:12:20,944 --> 00:12:22,304
Do you need a hand?

141
00:12:23,064 --> 00:12:25,385
I can put the suitcase away
for you tomorrow.

142
00:12:25,465 --> 00:12:26,585
Thanks.

143
00:12:27,625 --> 00:12:29,105
Is Nut asleep?

144
00:12:29,184 --> 00:12:30,785
Not yet.

145
00:12:30,865 --> 00:12:32,544
He's rather enthusiastic.

146
00:12:32,625 --> 00:12:34,665
He's reading Gen's book.

147
00:12:36,985 --> 00:12:40,785
I have to thank you for taking care of us.

148
00:12:41,385 --> 00:12:43,585
You don't have to thank me.

149
00:12:43,665 --> 00:12:46,145
Both of you take good care of me too.

150
00:12:47,544 --> 00:12:48,985
It's not the same.

151
00:12:52,785 --> 00:12:54,225
I may be…

152
00:12:54,704 --> 00:12:56,304
a little forgetful,

153
00:12:57,184 --> 00:12:59,985
but… I know my son well.

154
00:13:01,345 --> 00:13:04,025
Nut is a handful,

155
00:13:04,105 --> 00:13:05,985
especially when he's upset.

156
00:13:08,304 --> 00:13:10,184
I'm really thankful to you

157
00:13:12,385 --> 00:13:15,424
for accepting who he is and not giving up.

158
00:13:19,025 --> 00:13:20,865
From now on, my condition…

159
00:13:21,345 --> 00:13:22,824
will keep getting worse.

160
00:13:24,665 --> 00:13:26,865
I won't be the same and…

161
00:13:28,424 --> 00:13:30,585
I'll cause a lot more problems for him.

162
00:13:34,865 --> 00:13:36,944
I would like to ask you

163
00:13:38,184 --> 00:13:39,665
to stay calm

164
00:13:40,225 --> 00:13:41,625
and…

165
00:13:41,704 --> 00:13:44,225
forever remain so nice to our family.

166
00:13:46,665 --> 00:13:48,225
Don't leave Nut.

167
00:13:49,665 --> 00:13:54,465
I don't want him to lose another person
who he loves and loves him back.

168
00:13:59,064 --> 00:14:00,385
I promise.

169
00:14:01,465 --> 00:14:03,704
I'll stay and take care of you

170
00:14:03,785 --> 00:14:05,704
and take care of Nut.

171
00:14:05,785 --> 00:14:07,585
I'll never leave.

172
00:14:09,304 --> 00:14:11,345
I'll take care of Nut forever.

173
00:14:13,025 --> 00:14:14,665
It's not just my job,

174
00:14:15,625 --> 00:14:17,345
but it's my life's vocation.

175
00:14:22,064 --> 00:14:23,424
Thank you.

176
00:15:20,424 --> 00:15:23,184
You're as focused
as when you were studying for exams.

177
00:15:24,905 --> 00:15:26,944
Have you seen me studying for exams?

178
00:15:28,745 --> 00:15:29,865
Who knows?

179
00:15:29,944 --> 00:15:31,505
I might have seen you.

180
00:15:32,225 --> 00:15:33,785
You just didn't care about me.

181
00:15:36,025 --> 00:15:37,145
Come here, then.

182
00:15:39,064 --> 00:15:39,905
So…

183
00:15:39,985 --> 00:15:41,544
Read it to me.

184
00:15:42,584 --> 00:15:44,265
Your voice might make me less sad.

185
00:15:49,265 --> 00:15:52,145
"Your mother behaves
and speaks differently.

186
00:15:52,704 --> 00:15:54,184
After a checkup,

187
00:15:54,865 --> 00:15:56,865
Alzheimer's disease was diagnosed.

188
00:15:57,944 --> 00:15:59,905
The patient can still speak normally.

189
00:16:01,184 --> 00:16:02,865
Her memories remain.

190
00:16:03,985 --> 00:16:07,064
This means
she's still in the early stages."

191
00:16:09,785 --> 00:16:10,824
It says that…

192
00:16:11,464 --> 00:16:13,025
Mom will keep losing her memory

193
00:16:14,424 --> 00:16:15,944
and her ability to help herself.

194
00:16:18,105 --> 00:16:20,145
She'll forget how to chew.

195
00:16:22,225 --> 00:16:23,865
She'll even forget how to breathe.

196
00:16:26,464 --> 00:16:27,865
Don't be afraid.

197
00:16:29,424 --> 00:16:30,905
No matter what happens,

198
00:16:31,385 --> 00:16:32,704
we'll keep fighting.

199
00:16:34,985 --> 00:16:37,824
Let's make the rest of your mom's memories

200
00:16:38,464 --> 00:16:40,665
good memories.

201
00:16:44,824 --> 00:16:45,944
Thank you.

202
00:17:08,825 --> 00:17:11,024
UNCLE SAEN

203
00:17:23,785 --> 00:17:25,504
-Yes, Uncle Saen.
-Where are you?

204
00:17:26,184 --> 00:17:29,625
I just got off work.
We barely talked yesterday.

205
00:17:29,705 --> 00:17:31,225
I'll swing by to see you.

206
00:17:32,105 --> 00:17:33,385
I'm already home.

207
00:17:34,225 --> 00:17:35,264
Why so fast?

208
00:17:36,785 --> 00:17:38,625
My mom is sick.

209
00:17:38,705 --> 00:17:40,305
I took her to the hospital.

210
00:17:40,385 --> 00:17:41,785
What happened?

211
00:17:43,905 --> 00:17:45,345
She has Alzheimer's.

212
00:17:49,585 --> 00:17:51,305
You don't have to worry.

213
00:17:51,385 --> 00:17:52,744
I'll take care of her.

214
00:18:20,105 --> 00:18:20,984
Be careful.

215
00:18:25,945 --> 00:18:26,945
Kuenchai.

216
00:18:28,465 --> 00:18:30,105
Gosh.

217
00:18:30,185 --> 00:18:32,225
So noisy.

218
00:18:32,905 --> 00:18:34,545
Who's that?

219
00:18:35,185 --> 00:18:36,705
It's me.

220
00:18:40,225 --> 00:18:44,984
It feels so nice to have a wash.

221
00:18:45,065 --> 00:18:48,865
It was so stuffy in there.

222
00:18:48,945 --> 00:18:52,625
Was it your voice I heard the other day?

223
00:18:52,705 --> 00:18:57,865
I was the only one
who would wake up in that room.

224
00:18:58,865 --> 00:19:00,065
Wait a minute.

225
00:19:00,145 --> 00:19:01,984
Actually…

226
00:19:02,545 --> 00:19:03,504
Does this mean

227
00:19:03,585 --> 00:19:05,585
you've woken up before?

228
00:19:05,665 --> 00:19:06,705
When was that?

229
00:19:06,784 --> 00:19:09,065
I'm not sure.

230
00:19:09,145 --> 00:19:11,665
I remember that there were

231
00:19:11,744 --> 00:19:13,825
Mr. Sibmeun and Mrs. Na in the house.

232
00:19:13,905 --> 00:19:16,264
Mrs. Na was still pregnant with Nut.

233
00:19:16,345 --> 00:19:21,024
One day, they brought baby Nut home.

234
00:19:21,504 --> 00:19:23,345
He kept crying

235
00:19:23,425 --> 00:19:26,945
that Mr. Sibmeun and Mrs. Na
had to cradle him all night long.

236
00:19:30,185 --> 00:19:31,585
What's next?

237
00:19:31,665 --> 00:19:34,744
This house was filled
with happiness back then.

238
00:19:34,825 --> 00:19:37,504
Both of them loved Nut so much.

239
00:19:37,585 --> 00:19:41,744
Mrs. Na would tell him stories

240
00:19:41,825 --> 00:19:44,225
even when he was so young.

241
00:19:44,705 --> 00:19:47,905
Mr. Sib would buy him toys.

242
00:19:47,984 --> 00:19:49,945
But as Nut grew up,

243
00:19:50,504 --> 00:19:52,145
the two of them started to fight.

244
00:19:53,665 --> 00:19:56,105
Nut is a normal boy like anyone else.

245
00:19:56,905 --> 00:20:00,625
Can't you see how girly he is?

246
00:20:00,705 --> 00:20:05,225
After that, they didn't use me as much.

247
00:20:08,024 --> 00:20:09,465
It's probably because…

248
00:20:10,185 --> 00:20:12,744
you're a keepsake from Mr. Saen,

249
00:20:13,744 --> 00:20:15,545
so Mr. Sibmeun didn't want to see you.

250
00:20:16,784 --> 00:20:19,825
Mrs. Na put me in the closet.

251
00:20:19,905 --> 00:20:22,945
I would fall asleep from time to time.

252
00:20:23,024 --> 00:20:27,145
I remember a time
when I woke up because it was so hot.

253
00:20:30,065 --> 00:20:31,545
Do you love him?

254
00:20:35,065 --> 00:20:38,545
I almost died because of Mr. Sib.

255
00:20:39,264 --> 00:20:41,705
Thank goodness Mrs. Na saved me.

256
00:20:42,465 --> 00:20:47,225
After that day,
I was moved to the storage room,

257
00:20:47,784 --> 00:20:50,425
and I've been sleeping since.

258
00:21:10,784 --> 00:21:12,305
I'm sorry.

259
00:21:12,385 --> 00:21:14,264
I saw it in the storage room,

260
00:21:14,784 --> 00:21:16,625
so I washed it for you.

261
00:21:17,585 --> 00:21:19,065
I'll put it back

262
00:21:19,545 --> 00:21:21,705
once it's dry.

263
00:21:23,705 --> 00:21:24,825
That's okay.

264
00:21:26,065 --> 00:21:27,585
I don't use it anymore.

265
00:21:37,705 --> 00:21:38,945
I'll take a look.

266
00:22:08,145 --> 00:22:09,625
Hello, Uncle Saen.

267
00:22:10,825 --> 00:22:12,665
Go ahead. Mom is inside.

268
00:22:20,665 --> 00:22:22,145
Come here, Kuenchai.

269
00:22:49,065 --> 00:22:51,625
What do you think Mr. Saen is like
when he's angry?

270
00:22:55,665 --> 00:22:56,865
Why are you asking that?

271
00:23:00,264 --> 00:23:01,705
I'm just wondering.

272
00:23:02,544 --> 00:23:04,305
From what I know about him,

273
00:23:04,385 --> 00:23:06,825
he always seems kind and considerate.

274
00:23:10,105 --> 00:23:12,305
I can't imagine what it's like

275
00:23:13,544 --> 00:23:15,145
when someone like him gets mad.

276
00:23:19,105 --> 00:23:20,905
I don't see him that often,

277
00:23:21,865 --> 00:23:24,105
but he usually takes care of Mom and me.

278
00:23:25,865 --> 00:23:27,744
He really loves his family.

279
00:23:28,984 --> 00:23:30,504
He even stepped back for Dad

280
00:23:31,264 --> 00:23:32,465
when they fought over Mom.

281
00:23:34,264 --> 00:23:36,105
He didn't get mad when Dad made trouble.

282
00:23:37,185 --> 00:23:38,544
He's very calm.

283
00:23:39,544 --> 00:23:41,905
I've never seen him mad
except when it comes to Jan.

284
00:23:46,625 --> 00:23:48,185
I assume family members…

285
00:23:49,225 --> 00:23:50,625
wouldn't hurt each other.

286
00:23:52,865 --> 00:23:54,465
Are you worried about Jan?

287
00:23:57,825 --> 00:23:59,504
I don't know about his family,

288
00:24:02,024 --> 00:24:02,984
but I believe that…

289
00:24:04,825 --> 00:24:06,544
he's not the same as my dad.

290
00:24:12,905 --> 00:24:14,825
You seem livelier than I expected.

291
00:24:17,544 --> 00:24:19,145
I have no reason to be sad.

292
00:24:19,865 --> 00:24:21,865
Nut gets worried when I'm sad.

293
00:24:23,504 --> 00:24:25,465
This disease has made me realize

294
00:24:26,264 --> 00:24:29,385
that I don't have much time left
to live a life with memories.

295
00:24:30,465 --> 00:24:32,784
So I would rather use
the rest of my memories

296
00:24:33,744 --> 00:24:35,065
for good things

297
00:24:35,784 --> 00:24:37,425
and happy things.

298
00:24:46,665 --> 00:24:47,905
I'm sorry

299
00:24:49,705 --> 00:24:52,705
for being one of the reasons
that you ended up this way.

300
00:24:57,185 --> 00:24:58,225
Don't be.

301
00:24:59,065 --> 00:25:01,504
I know you've done a lot of things for me

302
00:25:04,504 --> 00:25:07,305
and helped relieve my sadness.

303
00:25:12,585 --> 00:25:15,385
I'm sick from my own doings.

304
00:25:16,585 --> 00:25:21,145
I blamed myself that my family suffered
because I chose the wrong husband.

305
00:25:24,024 --> 00:25:25,665
I felt sorry for myself,

306
00:25:27,425 --> 00:25:28,504
for Sibmeun,

307
00:25:29,984 --> 00:25:30,825
for Nut,

308
00:25:34,105 --> 00:25:35,185
and for you.

309
00:25:37,744 --> 00:25:39,504
Those feelings didn't just…

310
00:25:40,105 --> 00:25:42,024
weaken my heart,

311
00:25:44,225 --> 00:25:46,065
they destroyed my body.

312
00:25:47,385 --> 00:25:48,865
It's a shame

313
00:25:50,744 --> 00:25:52,345
that I realized this too late.

314
00:25:53,984 --> 00:25:56,345
Had I fixed it earlier,

315
00:25:58,385 --> 00:25:59,984
I wouldn't have suffered

316
00:26:00,945 --> 00:26:03,825
and I wouldn't have been sick
all this time.

317
00:26:22,024 --> 00:26:23,625
I'll forget it soon enough.

318
00:26:26,465 --> 00:26:28,425
You'll probably suffer more

319
00:26:28,945 --> 00:26:30,345
since you remember all of it.

320
00:26:35,225 --> 00:26:38,825
If you don't want
a twisted, tormented life like mine,

321
00:26:41,105 --> 00:26:43,304
you'll have to live mindfully.

322
00:26:44,065 --> 00:26:46,425
Correct your mistakes while you still can.

323
00:26:48,065 --> 00:26:51,665
Don't neglect them
and drown in regret like I did.

324
00:26:54,625 --> 00:26:56,744
I don't want you to end up like me.

325
00:27:19,145 --> 00:27:20,744
Thank you for visiting Mom.

326
00:27:22,905 --> 00:27:24,865
I don't know if I can come again.

327
00:27:26,024 --> 00:27:29,264
It will be even harder on you from now on,

328
00:27:29,345 --> 00:27:31,304
having to take care of two sick people.

329
00:27:32,264 --> 00:27:35,065
You can call me whenever you need to.

330
00:27:37,625 --> 00:27:39,145
One person lost his memory.

331
00:27:40,185 --> 00:27:41,825
Another person is losing hers.

332
00:27:43,705 --> 00:27:45,065
Who knows?

333
00:27:45,625 --> 00:27:47,705
I might remember something soon.

334
00:27:55,225 --> 00:27:56,705
Actually,

335
00:27:56,784 --> 00:27:58,504
I'm starting to see more things.

336
00:27:59,905 --> 00:28:02,145
I can't piece them together just yet,

337
00:28:03,825 --> 00:28:05,225
but I think

338
00:28:05,905 --> 00:28:07,825
I might remember everything soon.

339
00:28:09,225 --> 00:28:10,665
When that time comes,

340
00:28:11,744 --> 00:28:13,105
I might find out

341
00:28:13,825 --> 00:28:15,665
what happened to Tatarn.

342
00:28:21,905 --> 00:28:23,345
That would be great.

343
00:28:24,225 --> 00:28:25,865
Tarn's case will finally progress.

344
00:28:29,145 --> 00:28:30,865
I don't know

345
00:28:30,945 --> 00:28:32,825
why Tatarn was attacked,

346
00:28:34,264 --> 00:28:35,544
but nobody

347
00:28:36,064 --> 00:28:37,744
should be harmed, should they?

348
00:28:42,825 --> 00:28:44,064
Not everyone

349
00:28:44,665 --> 00:28:45,984
is blessed with humanity.

350
00:28:47,225 --> 00:28:48,465
People can hurt each other

351
00:28:48,544 --> 00:28:50,225
over simple disagreements.

352
00:28:50,784 --> 00:28:52,905
Conflicts of interest

353
00:28:52,984 --> 00:28:54,504
can lead to murder.

354
00:28:57,425 --> 00:28:59,185
When we disagree,

355
00:28:59,264 --> 00:29:01,225
shouldn't we talk about it reasonably?

356
00:29:02,585 --> 00:29:04,264
Shouldn't we try to understand

357
00:29:05,585 --> 00:29:07,225
rather than fight?

358
00:29:21,385 --> 00:29:24,145
-A fractured skull and a hemorrhage?
-Excuse me, sir.

359
00:29:26,544 --> 00:29:29,784
We found no fingerprints
on the vase or the broken pieces.

360
00:29:30,264 --> 00:29:31,865
Here's the report.

361
00:29:35,825 --> 00:29:38,064
They probably thought
that it was well planned.

362
00:29:38,865 --> 00:29:42,145
They must have thought
that they destroyed all the evidence.

363
00:29:42,225 --> 00:29:43,625
Unfortunately,

364
00:29:43,705 --> 00:29:46,865
they dropped some evidence
in the cactus pot.

365
00:29:56,984 --> 00:29:58,304
It doesn't weigh much.

366
00:29:59,064 --> 00:30:00,504
Why was his injury so severe?

367
00:30:01,744 --> 00:30:03,465
Or, is the weapon not the vase?

368
00:30:08,585 --> 00:30:10,145
According to the report,

369
00:30:11,064 --> 00:30:14,024
if the weapon is really
a blunt, hard object like you said,

370
00:30:15,185 --> 00:30:17,145
and if it's the vase in this photo,

371
00:30:17,784 --> 00:30:21,825
could it really cause
a fractured skull and a hemorrhage?

372
00:30:22,665 --> 00:30:23,825
That's right.

373
00:30:24,425 --> 00:30:26,385
The vase would break after one hit.

374
00:30:26,465 --> 00:30:28,544
The injuries suggest multiple hits.

375
00:30:30,465 --> 00:30:33,264
I confirm that I diagnosed
according to his symptoms.

376
00:30:33,345 --> 00:30:36,264
A combination of things
could have caused the injuries,

377
00:30:36,345 --> 00:30:38,945
not just the weapon's weight or shape,

378
00:30:39,024 --> 00:30:41,064
It also depends on force

379
00:30:41,145 --> 00:30:42,024
and other factors.

380
00:30:42,665 --> 00:30:43,784
Unless

381
00:30:43,865 --> 00:30:46,105
the weapon is not just this vase,

382
00:30:47,225 --> 00:30:48,264
but another as well.

383
00:30:54,585 --> 00:30:56,665
You'll have to live mindfully.

384
00:30:57,625 --> 00:30:59,825
Correct your mistakes while you still can.

385
00:31:00,705 --> 00:31:04,585
Don't neglect them
and drown in regret like I did.

386
00:31:04,665 --> 00:31:06,064
Not everyone

387
00:31:06,585 --> 00:31:08,145
is blessed with humanity.

388
00:31:09,264 --> 00:31:10,625
People can hurt each other

389
00:31:10,705 --> 00:31:12,185
over simple disagreements.

390
00:31:12,264 --> 00:31:13,425
Conflicts of interest

391
00:31:14,304 --> 00:31:15,585
can lead to murder.

392
00:31:15,665 --> 00:31:17,744
Shouldn't we try to understand

393
00:31:17,825 --> 00:31:19,705
rather than fight?

394
00:31:26,264 --> 00:31:27,225
Yes.

395
00:31:28,465 --> 00:31:30,784
I just got back. I'm at the parking lot.

396
00:31:33,504 --> 00:31:34,544
I just found out

397
00:31:35,185 --> 00:31:37,945
that you let people into that house.

398
00:31:38,905 --> 00:31:41,504
The police called. I couldn't refuse.

399
00:31:42,504 --> 00:31:44,024
The issue was dying down.

400
00:31:44,705 --> 00:31:47,345
People were forgetting about it,
but you dug it back up.

401
00:31:49,304 --> 00:31:51,145
You can't blame it all on me.

402
00:31:51,705 --> 00:31:53,905
This whole thing happened
all because of you.

403
00:31:53,984 --> 00:31:57,064
Get out! No more deforestation.

404
00:31:57,145 --> 00:32:00,145
Get out! No more deforestation.

405
00:32:00,225 --> 00:32:03,824
Get out! We don't want it. Is that right?

406
00:32:03,905 --> 00:32:05,264
We don't want it. Get out!

407
00:32:19,024 --> 00:32:20,185
Yes, Dad.

408
00:32:23,744 --> 00:32:25,185
Don't worry.

409
00:32:25,264 --> 00:32:27,064
I'll handle it as soon as possible.

410
00:32:32,304 --> 00:32:34,345
Is the leader your wife's nephew?

411
00:32:35,945 --> 00:32:38,744
-Yes. I warned him--
-Tell him to stop.

412
00:32:42,185 --> 00:32:44,024
The board is getting upset.

413
00:32:45,024 --> 00:32:48,585
You know how much we paid him
to settle this deal.

414
00:32:49,665 --> 00:32:52,824
It cannot fail from these stupid ideals.

415
00:32:58,744 --> 00:33:02,345
I'm not sure if he'll listen.
He's pretty stubborn.

416
00:33:02,425 --> 00:33:04,024
I don't care what he is.

417
00:33:05,105 --> 00:33:07,425
All I care about
is that we continue this project.

418
00:33:09,064 --> 00:33:10,225
If he doesn't stop,

419
00:33:11,225 --> 00:33:12,185
you'll have to.

420
00:33:13,744 --> 00:33:14,945
You…

421
00:33:15,945 --> 00:33:18,744
Your future at TRD depends on yourself.

422
00:33:22,784 --> 00:33:25,105
You ordered me to do it.

423
00:33:26,504 --> 00:33:29,865
I did, but you didn't succeed.

424
00:33:29,945 --> 00:33:31,905
I had to clean up for you.

425
00:33:32,504 --> 00:33:35,425
I kept him alive for your sake.

426
00:33:35,504 --> 00:33:37,504
That's why this is all messed up.

427
00:33:41,304 --> 00:33:44,064
Right now, my father, the board,

428
00:33:44,145 --> 00:33:46,264
and the investors are all pressuring me.

429
00:33:46,345 --> 00:33:48,185
And the police are snooping around.

430
00:33:49,865 --> 00:33:51,145
I have to do something

431
00:33:51,225 --> 00:33:53,105
before we're all ruined.

432
00:33:53,665 --> 00:33:54,544
What will you do?

433
00:33:57,905 --> 00:34:00,905
If your wife's nephew is such a nuisance,

434
00:34:04,705 --> 00:34:06,585
I'll end it myself.

435
00:34:12,944 --> 00:34:15,665
The book that Nut
was reading yesterday said that

436
00:34:16,264 --> 00:34:19,185
this seemingly harmless disease

437
00:34:19,665 --> 00:34:22,225
can eat up the patient

438
00:34:23,025 --> 00:34:24,864
and spit out the empty shell

439
00:34:25,625 --> 00:34:28,424
without the person's identity inside.

440
00:34:29,705 --> 00:34:31,304
The movie Nut watched the other day

441
00:34:31,985 --> 00:34:33,505
also said

442
00:34:33,585 --> 00:34:35,225
that cancer is better than this.

443
00:34:36,225 --> 00:34:38,065
It sounds terrifying,

444
00:34:39,625 --> 00:34:41,665
but seeing her now…

445
00:34:45,625 --> 00:34:46,784
You're awake.

446
00:34:47,585 --> 00:34:48,784
Yes.

447
00:34:48,864 --> 00:34:50,944
Nut went to bed late, so he isn't up yet.

448
00:34:52,025 --> 00:34:54,025
What are you doing
so early in the morning?

449
00:34:55,065 --> 00:34:57,145
I wake up early every day.

450
00:34:57,665 --> 00:35:00,665
You and Nut are the only ones
who always wake up late.

451
00:35:04,465 --> 00:35:06,505
-I was meaning to ask.
-Yes?

452
00:35:06,585 --> 00:35:08,384
Do you like wood sorrels?

453
00:35:09,345 --> 00:35:10,625
Well…

454
00:35:18,025 --> 00:35:20,585
It's a flower that sticks in my memory.

455
00:35:22,545 --> 00:35:24,545
I used to live in Soi Butterfly,

456
00:35:25,025 --> 00:35:28,985
and that alley was lined
with wood sorrels.

457
00:35:31,384 --> 00:35:34,225
That was what they called the alley.

458
00:35:36,585 --> 00:35:38,825
When I first moved here,

459
00:35:39,785 --> 00:35:42,384
I felt a little out of place,

460
00:35:42,465 --> 00:35:43,904
so I planted these here.

461
00:35:45,345 --> 00:35:49,864
These flowers made this place feel
warm and familiar like the old house.

462
00:35:53,625 --> 00:35:56,265
I'm used to this house now, though.

463
00:35:57,145 --> 00:35:58,265
And I…

464
00:35:58,985 --> 00:36:01,825
love this house as much as the old one.

465
00:36:04,265 --> 00:36:06,384
A house that is a home.

466
00:36:13,345 --> 00:36:14,785
I like this house too.

467
00:36:15,904 --> 00:36:18,225
I also like that you're cheerful.

468
00:36:24,705 --> 00:36:27,345
I know Nut and you are worried about me.

469
00:36:28,785 --> 00:36:30,625
But since my disease can't be cured,

470
00:36:31,225 --> 00:36:33,505
don't worry about curing it.

471
00:36:35,985 --> 00:36:39,065
The drugs are just slowing it down,

472
00:36:39,985 --> 00:36:42,185
but my body worsens every day.

473
00:36:45,265 --> 00:36:47,025
I think…

474
00:36:48,625 --> 00:36:50,465
From now on, let's live.

475
00:36:51,985 --> 00:36:53,665
Through both joy and sorrow…

476
00:36:56,384 --> 00:36:59,985
until my memories fade away.

477
00:37:06,864 --> 00:37:08,585
I read somewhere

478
00:37:10,065 --> 00:37:13,305
that the thing that Alzheimer's
can't take away from us…

479
00:37:14,384 --> 00:37:15,745
is love.

480
00:37:21,985 --> 00:37:24,705
Sometimes, the sooner we accept the truth,

481
00:37:25,545 --> 00:37:28,065
the sooner our wound heals.

482
00:37:43,665 --> 00:37:45,625
THIS WAY TO THE BEDROOM

483
00:37:56,904 --> 00:37:58,185
What's this?

484
00:38:00,065 --> 00:38:03,305
I registered your information
at The Mirror Foundation,

485
00:38:03,944 --> 00:38:06,265
and they gave us this wristband.

486
00:38:06,904 --> 00:38:08,944
It's filled with all of your information.

487
00:38:09,545 --> 00:38:13,065
In case you get lost
and someone finds you,

488
00:38:13,145 --> 00:38:14,864
they'll know where to drop you off.

489
00:38:15,745 --> 00:38:16,745
So…

490
00:38:16,825 --> 00:38:18,464
you must wear it at all times.

491
00:38:18,545 --> 00:38:19,505
Don't take it off.

492
00:38:31,265 --> 00:38:32,904
Next.

493
00:38:32,985 --> 00:38:34,825
-What's it?
-The number is…

494
00:38:34,904 --> 00:38:37,225
-Sixty-two.
-Sixty-two.

495
00:38:37,305 --> 00:38:38,785
-I have it.
-You do.

496
00:38:38,864 --> 00:38:41,265
-I have it, too.
-I don't.

497
00:38:42,545 --> 00:38:43,545
This one.

498
00:38:44,145 --> 00:38:45,225
What's the number?

499
00:38:47,345 --> 00:38:48,705
-Forty-six.
-Forty-six.

500
00:38:48,785 --> 00:38:50,225
-I have it.
-What?

501
00:38:50,305 --> 00:38:51,864
Why don't I have it?

502
00:38:55,745 --> 00:38:56,904
Wait a minute.

503
00:38:58,025 --> 00:39:00,145
-Kuenchai got bingo.
-What?

504
00:39:00,225 --> 00:39:03,464
-Oh, wow. Great job.
-That's awesome.

505
00:39:05,105 --> 00:39:06,145
Great job.

506
00:39:06,225 --> 00:39:08,384
Give me your hand.

507
00:39:08,464 --> 00:39:10,305
-Great job.
-Another one.

508
00:39:10,384 --> 00:39:12,145
Since it can't be avoided,

509
00:39:12,225 --> 00:39:13,745
we'll hold onto it.

510
00:39:14,265 --> 00:39:16,345
We'll use this pain as an opportunity

511
00:39:17,025 --> 00:39:19,145
to bring us even closer.

512
00:39:34,745 --> 00:39:36,145
It smells so good.

513
00:39:36,225 --> 00:39:38,065
What are you making today?

514
00:39:39,904 --> 00:39:41,705
Tofu with tamarind sauce.

515
00:39:43,145 --> 00:39:44,185
What?

516
00:39:48,424 --> 00:39:49,585
-Mom.
-What?

517
00:39:49,665 --> 00:39:51,705
You got Tofu all confused.

518
00:39:53,585 --> 00:39:56,185
I only heard of eggs with tamarind sauce.

519
00:39:56,825 --> 00:39:58,065
Well,

520
00:39:58,145 --> 00:39:59,705
they're similar.

521
00:39:59,785 --> 00:40:01,785
I changed the eggs to tofu.

522
00:40:05,025 --> 00:40:07,384
I like the name of this dish.

523
00:40:11,585 --> 00:40:12,825
So…

524
00:40:12,904 --> 00:40:14,985
what are the ingredients?

525
00:40:15,585 --> 00:40:17,545
There is

526
00:40:18,025 --> 00:40:19,345
hard tofu.

527
00:40:19,904 --> 00:40:22,025
There are also red onions,

528
00:40:22,825 --> 00:40:24,185
dried chili,

529
00:40:24,265 --> 00:40:26,025
and…

530
00:40:29,424 --> 00:40:30,305
Here, Mom.

531
00:40:30,864 --> 00:40:33,424
There's cilantro, tamarind,

532
00:40:33,505 --> 00:40:34,985
and palm sugar.

533
00:40:35,545 --> 00:40:38,185
Some recipes also add garlic and sesame.

534
00:40:40,745 --> 00:40:41,904
-Mom.
-What?

535
00:40:41,985 --> 00:40:44,305
Should we try new recipes someday?

536
00:40:44,384 --> 00:40:45,785
There is a lot here.

537
00:40:45,864 --> 00:40:47,145
Sounds good.

538
00:40:48,464 --> 00:40:50,305
-Should I help?
-Sure.

539
00:40:52,025 --> 00:40:53,944
What are there?

540
00:40:54,025 --> 00:40:55,025
Here.

541
00:40:55,585 --> 00:40:56,944
The bread looks delicious.

542
00:40:57,025 --> 00:40:59,545
The sweets look good.

543
00:40:59,625 --> 00:41:00,785
What sweet?

544
00:41:00,864 --> 00:41:02,025
What does it say?

